div.p:
2. The Magnificence of its Building;
                     Anno 1086. 
                  William of Malmesbury, informeth us; That the beauty of St. Pauls Church is ſo magnificent that it deſerves, to be numbered in the Rank of excellent Edifices: ſo large is that arched Vault underneath, and the Church above it of ſuch Capacity, that it may ſeem ſufficient to receive any multitude of people whatſoever.
